  "marketPositioning": "RustyTube is positioned as an open-source, performance-oriented desktop YouTube client built with Rust and Tauri. It differentiates itself from browser-based access and Electron-based alternatives by leveraging Rust for potentially better performance and a more native feel. It aims to provide a privacy-conscious viewing experience, aligning with other alternative clients, and plans to incorporate features like ad blocking (via SponsorBlock) and full playlist support to enhance user control over the viewing experience."
